#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:8
msgid ""
"Make sure you understand the code from :ref:`sprites`. The example code "
"there is great to get started with."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:10
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Create a player-character sprite. Pick your own image for the sprite, "
"from the web or from Kenney.nl."
msgstr ""
"Erstelle ein Sprite für die Spielfigur. Wähle dein eigenes Bild für das "
"Sprite."

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:12
msgid ""
"Allow the user to move the player move by the keyboard, mouse, or game "
"pad. Your choice. If you use the mouse, make sure you hide the cursor. "
"The :ref:`sprites` chapter uses the mouse, you can also look at the "
"examples on the Arcade website for `Sprite Player Movement "
"<https://arcade.academy/examples/index.html#sprite-player-movement>`_. "
"These examples show mouse, keyboard, improved keyboard, and the game "
"controller."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:18
#, fuzzy
msgid "Create \"good\" sprites. Pick your own image for the good sprite."
msgstr "Erstelle \"gute\" Sprites. Wähle dein eigenes Bild für das Sprite."

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:19
msgid ""
"For each good sprite collected, make the score go up. Play a 'good' sound"
" when the user collects that item."
msgstr ""
"Erhöhe die Punktzahl für jedes eingesammelte gute Sprite. Spiele einen "
"\"guten\" Sound ab, wenn der Benutzer diesen Gegenstand sammelt."

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:21
#, fuzzy
msgid "Create \"bad\" sprites. Pick your own image for the bad sprite."
msgstr "Erstelle \"böse\" Sprites. Wählen dein eigenes Bild für das Sprite."

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:22
msgid ""
"For each bad sprite touched, have the score go down. Play a 'bad' sound "
"when the user collects that item."
msgstr ""
"Lasse für jedes böse Sprite die Punktzahl sinken. Spiele einen "
"\"schlechten\" Sound ab, wenn der Benutzer diesen Gegenstand einsammelt."

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:25
msgid "A common mistake at this stage is to overwrite your list:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:27
msgid ""
"hit_list = arcade.check_for_collision_with_list(self.player_sprite, "
"self.good_sprite_list)\n"
"hit_list = arcade.check_for_collision_with_list(self.player_sprite, "
"self.bad_sprite_list)\n"
"for good_sprite in hit_list:\n"
"    # Process\n"
"for bad_sprite in hit_list:\n"
"    # Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:36
msgid ""
"This would cause bad sprites to be processed twice, because the original "
"`hit_list` is overwritten. Instead try:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:39
msgid ""
"hit_list = arcade.check_for_collision_with_list(self.player_sprite, "
"self.good_sprite_list)\n"
"for good_sprite in hit_list:\n"
"    # Process\n"
"hit_list = arcade.check_for_collision_with_list(self.player_sprite, "
"self.bad_sprite_list)\n"
"for bad_sprite in hit_list:\n"
"    # Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:48
msgid "or:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:50
msgid ""
"good_hit_list = arcade.check_for_collision_with_list(self.player_sprite, "
"self.good_sprite_list)\n"
"bad_hit_list = arcade.check_for_collision_with_list(self.player_sprite, "
"self.bad_sprite_list)\n"
"for good_sprite in good_hit_list:\n"
"    # Process\n"
"for bad_sprite in bad_hit_list:\n"
"    # Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:59
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Animate/move the good sprites. Pick any of the motions we showed, such as"
" move and reset, bounce, go in circles, or a pattern. You can even make "
"your own. Try a sine-waves!"
msgstr ""
"Animiere/bewege die guten Sprites. Wähle eine der gezeigten Bewegungen "
"aus oder erstelle eine eigene."

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:62
msgid "Move the bad sprites. Move them differently than the good ones."
msgstr "Bewege die bösen Sprites. Bewege sie anders als die Guten."

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:63
msgid ""
"If the length of the good sprite list is zero, then don't move any of the"
" sprites or the character. \"Freeze\" the game. To do this, note what "
"line of the ``update`` method in the main window class causes the sprites"
" to move. Then only run that line if you have sprites. (Check the length "
"of the sprite list.) If you get that to work, the do something similar "
"``on_mouse_motion``."
msgstr ""
"Wenn die Länge der Liste der guten Sprites Null ist, verschiebe die "
"Sprites oder die Spielfigur nicht mehr. \"Friere\" das Spiel ein. Beachte"
" dazu, in welcher Zeile der Methode ``update`` in der Hauptfensterklasse "
"die Sprites verschoben werden. Führe diese Zeile dann nur aus, wenn du "
"gute Sprites hast. (Überprüfe die Länge der Sprite-Liste.) Wenn du das "
"zum Laufen gebracht hast, tue etwas Ähnliches in ``on_mouse_motion``."

#: ../../source/labs/lab_08_sprites/sprites.rst:68
msgid ""
"If the length of the good sprite list is zero, draw \"Game Over\" on the "
"screen."
msgstr ""
"Wenn die Länge der guten Sprite-Liste Null ist, zeichne \"Game Over\" auf"
" dem Bildschirm."

